costs, of $306 and favorable volumes of $78, partially oﬀset by higher costs of $112 and an unfavorable
currency impact of $7. Higher costs were driven by inﬂation, planned maintenance, and higher incentive
compensation. Operating margin of 26.8% increased 490 bp from 21.9% in the prior year primarily due
