20. SHARE-BASED COMPENSA TION
Our outstanding share-based compensation programs include deferred stock units and stock options.
During the ﬁscal year ended 30 September 2023, we granted market-based and time-based deferred
stock units. We have not issued stock option awards since ﬁscal year 2015. Under all programs, the
terms of the awards are ﬁxed at the grant date. We issue shares from treasury stock upon the payout of
deferred stock units and the exercise of stock options. As of 30 September 2023, there were 1.3 million
shares available for future grant under our Long-Term Incentive Plan ("LTIP"), which is shareholder
approved.
