Deferred tax liabilities related to "Intangible assets" decreased primarily due to the impact of capitalizing
research and development expenditures for U.S tax purposes. Deferred tax liabilities related to "Plant
and equipment" increased due to the impact of accelerated tax depreciation deductions in excess of
book depreciation, primarily in the United States. The increase was partially oﬀset with book charges in
excess of tax related to our business and asset actions that included certain costs for which we could not
recognize an income tax beneﬁt and were subject to a valuation allowance.
Deferred tax assets for "Tax loss carryforwards" increased primarily due to losses in certain Chinese
subsidiaries. A portion of these losses were subject to a valuation allowance for which we could not
recognize an income tax beneﬁt. The deferred tax components for "Reserves and accruals" and "Other"
were impacted by changes in tax deferred deductions and the timing of revenue recognition for local tax
and accounting purposes.
